data.title: Elections: Finnish Parliament 2023 General
data.text:
Chief of State: President Sauli NIINISTO (since 1 March 2012)

Head of Government: Prime Minister Sanna MARIN (since 10 December 2019)

The President is directly elected by absolute majority vote in up to two rounds. The president may serve up to two 6-year terms.

199 members of Parliament are directly elected in single and multi-seat constituencies via proportional representation vote. The remaining member, who represents the autonomous region of Ã…land, is directly elected by plurality vote. All members serve 4-year terms.
